Game.....: Heavy Metal Geomatrix
Origin...: USA - NTSC
Released.: September 18th, 2001
Ripped.......: NADA

War is waged inside the Geomatrix with Nanobots armed with devastating weaponry. To win you must fight, to live you must win!

Step inside the Geomatrix!
In the future, with the evolution of Nanobot technology, microscopic robots recreate human cell composition in the cyber world. Fantasy and reality have merged into one neo-world. Humans abandon the real world for the cyber luxury of the virtual world. With their backs turned on reality, they never saw the catastrophe coming.

Now, most natural resources have been stolen, the polar caps are dislodged and melting, submerging mother earth underwater. What little turf remains is claimed by thugs, gangs, and mercenaries. The battle for landmass begins. 

Four teams of Nanobot warriors clash in futuristic 3-D arenas for the pursuit of land

Choose from 12 different Nano-Gladiators to battle it out in the post-apocalyptic Geomatrix

Cool characters based on creations by renowned artist Simon Bisley, and edgy 3-D graphics

Features a blistering metal soundtrack with newsongs from Megadeth, Halford, Corrosion of Conformity, WASP, Entomed, and Dust to Dust

Enjoy the USA release of this fine game we brought you the JAP version of in July. 